Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I think the common code replication in this case is fine, if not good.  In tests with such a small amount of code I would rather have such things localized in the event that the tests need to change for whatever reason. Further each is easier to understand IMHO this way.  However that is just personal opinion and I could see either side.  If you feel that Zhi's suggested comments are of value I would like to see them addressed independent of any further problems.  In other words: I would like to steer us away from accepting the argument that: "this is worth fixing if I can slip it in with something more important" and sticking with "lets do the right thing", especially when regarding such a minimal change.  But again, to clarify, I like it the way it is.
